sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant React UI
    participant Go API
    participant DB

    User->>React UI: Clicks "Login"

    alt Path A: Standard Password Login
        React UI->>Go API: POST /api/login {user, pass}
        Go API->>DB: Verify Hash
        alt MFA Enabled
            Go API-->>React UI: 401 Unauthorized { "mfa_required": true, "temp_token" }
            React UI->>User: Prompt for 6-digit TOTP Code
            User->>React UI: Enters Code
            React UI->>Go API: POST /api/login/mfa {code, temp_token}
            Go API->>Go API: Validate TOTP
            Go API-->>React UI: 200 OK + JWT Access/Refresh Tokens
        else MFA Disabled
            Go API-->>React UI: 200 OK + JWT Tokens
        end
    end

    alt Path B: Biometric / WebAuthn Login
        React UI->>Go API: GET /api/webauthn/login/begin
        Go API-->>React UI: Cryptographic Challenge
        React UI->>User: Browser prompts TouchID/FaceID
        User->>React UI: Biometric Approval
        React UI->>Go API: POST /api/webauthn/login/finish {signed_challenge}
        Go API->>DB: Verify Signature against stored Public Key
        Go API-->>React UI: 200 OK + JWT Tokens
    end

    Note over React UI, Go API: React stores JWT in memory & handles auto-refresh via POST /api/refresh